H0.text: Enzymes are the catalysts found in living organisms.

H1.text: Proteins are catalysts in living things.

H2.text: Carbohydrates are the catalysts found in living things.

A3.text: Enzymes are known to catalyze over 5,000 types of biochemical reactions.

A4.text: Other biological catalysts include catalytic RNA molecules, or ribozymes, which are sometimes classified as enzymes despite being composed of RNA rather than protein.
